## Selenium with Python 

Selenium Introduction

Selenium is suite of tools that is used to automate browser actions. It is framework for testing web applicaitons. 

Consists of following tools:
1. __Selenium IDE__ - Firefox addon to record and playback tests 
2. __Selenium Remote Control(RC) or Selenium 1__ - It is the initial version of selenium. JavaScript Program called Selenium core which                                                        controls the browser
3. __Selenium Grid__ - It is used to run multiple tests across different browsers, operating systems, and machines in parallel
4. __Selenium webdriver or Selenium 2__ - Selenium WebDriver tool is used to automate web application testing to verify that it works as                                             expected. It supports many browsers such as Firefox, Chrome, IE, and Safari.
